item.description: North Carolina Republican Mark Robinson hired attorney Jesse Binnall to lead an expeditious investigation into claims he made comments on a porn site.

item.title: Sen. Ron Johnson to Newsmax: Feds 'Continue to Stonewall' Butler Probe
item.description: The Secret Service and FBI are continuing to "stonewall and slow walk" the congressional investigation into the attempted assassination of former President Donald Trump in Butler, Pennsylvania, including on his would-be assassin, Thomas Crooks, Sen. Ron Johnson told Newsmax...

item.title: RedState Sports Report: Caitlin Clark Is Out of the WNBA Playoffs and So Are We
Democrat senator targeted by deepfake impersonator of Ukrainian official on Zoom call: reports
item.description: An individual impersonating the Ukrainian minister of foreign affairs reportedly contacted Democratic Sen. Benjamin Cardin this week, pressing him for foreign policy information.

item.title: Blaine Holt to Newsmax: Harris 'Welded' to Support for Ukraine
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris will likely treat Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy in a much warmer way during his visit to the White House than how she greeted Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, as she's "welded" to the administration's support for Ukraine.

item.description: Donald Trump hit Vice President Kamala Harris with a "Project 2025" of her own on Thursday, saying she supports citizenship for "20 million illegals."

item.title: BREAKING: NYC Mayor Eric Adams Indicted on Criminal Charges, Expected to be Arrested
Trump, Harris neck and neck in key states Arizona, Georgia, North Carolina: poll
item.description: The crucial battleground states of Arizona, Georgia and North Carolina are tossups for Vice President Kamala Harris and former President Donald Trump, a new poll says.

item.title: Appeals Court Hears Arguments Over Trump's $454M Civil Fraud Judgment
item.description: Donald Trump's lawyers on Thursday will seek to persuade a New York state appeals court to toss a nearly half-billion dollar judgment against the former U.S. president over real estate business practices a court has declared fraudulent.

item.title: Trump, Harris Vie for Crypto Voters
item.description: The rise in digital currency has Vice President Kamala Harris and former President Donald Trump each seeking to win over the latest American voting bloc, the "crypto voter.
